platformAttributes.ios.subtitle.k: 製作令人難以置信的機器人。
素晴らしいロボットを作りましょう。

platformAttributes.ios.editorialNotes.ta.k: 以精細組件創造趣怪機械人
打造專屬機器人 激發想像力

platformAttributes.ios.editorialNotes.st.k: ボディや腕などパーツを組み合わせて自分だけのロボットを作る「タイニーバップのロボット工場」。腕にはドリルや火炎放射器、足にはキャタピラ、さらには羽やプロペラまで。種類の豊富なパーツが創作意欲をかきたてる。色を付けて完成したら外で試運転してまた改造。正統派からユニークなものまで、思いのままに作ってみよう。

Kids (and kids at heart) can unleash their inner scientists with this captivatingly clever robot-creation kit, which features millions of different combinations for mechanical inventions. Whether you’re assembling a wheeled bot with laser guns for arms or a jolly jumping automaton with pogo-stick legs, taking your new bot on a walk through the woods will highlight the success—or the rough edges—of your design. While The Robot Factory teaches some nifty physics basics, we like to play around just for the pure fun of it.

This debut app in Tinybop’s Digital Toys series lets kids create, test and put into action whatever they can imagine. Scientists-in-training can construct thousands of physics-driven robots—from lizards and wizards to dancers and doctors—using 100 different interchangeable parts, then test them in real-world scenarios. Experiment with motion, colour, sound and function, then for extra fun, make your robots dance. A kid-friendly multi-user system encourages budding creators of all ages to flex their imagination, then show off their robot masterpieces in a special showroom.
